1
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:11,845
♪

2
00:00:13,430 --> 00:01:42,060
♪

3
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:47,649
We interrupt our
regular broadcast

4
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:50,235
to bring you some
breaking news from downtown.

5
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:52,070
We'll now take you
to Ms. Hasegawa,

6
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,697
who's already on the scene.

7
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:55,240
Ms. Hasegawa, can you hear me?

8
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,908
Yes I can, loud and clear.

9
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:58,910
Can you tell me what's
going on down there?

10
00:01:58,910 --> 00:02:00,620
A young boy is
climbing the tower.

11
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,331
Rescue workers are on their way,

12
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:05,417
but he isn't showing
any signs of stopping.

13
00:02:05,417 --> 00:02:06,752
Please let me through!

14
00:02:06,752 --> 00:02:08,920
Excuse me, I'm family!

15
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,381
(child wailing)

16
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,092
Ringo!

17
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:20,891
Rika, I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to!

18
00:02:20,891 --> 00:02:23,185
"Please don't do it," I said.

19
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:26,063
I tried to stop him!

20
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,484
(delighted chuckle)

21
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:36,365
♪

22
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:39,076
So you finally
decided to show up.

23
00:02:39,076 --> 00:02:42,621
We were starting to think
you'd given up on us.

24
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:44,081
Now, I'm no math whiz

25
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:47,542
but it looks like you're
a tad shy of 33 people.

26
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,127
Oh, I'm sorry, but‐‐

27
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:50,712
No, don't worry.

28
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:52,923
It's fine, no big deal.

29
00:02:52,923 --> 00:02:56,968
But I hope you know
what you're getting into.

30
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,054
Things could get
a little messy

31
00:02:59,054 --> 00:03:00,138
if he doesn't make it.

32
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,140
Bone fractures,
internal bleeding,

33
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,935
ruptured organs,
and that's if you're lucky.

34
00:03:04,935 --> 00:03:08,146
He could land on your head.

35
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:10,649
We'll lie down for ya, kid!

36
00:03:10,649 --> 00:03:12,818
♪

37
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:14,444
Gonzo?

38
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,029
Inuyama?

39
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:17,197
Mitsuru?

40
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:18,365
Natsumi too?

41
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:20,033
You came.

42
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,535
Hey, whatsa matter, babyface?

43
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:22,828
You look surprised to see us.

44
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:24,246
You didn't think
all your old pals

45
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:26,289
were gonna miss out on
your big moment, did ya?

46
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,667
You're lucky you
got friends like us.

47
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,169
You worry about jumpin',
we'll handle the rest.

48
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:34,214
‐Okay!
‐Hey, not so fast!

49
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,757
You see, Ikki?

50
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,342
We all believe in you.

51
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,010
You know you can do it.

52
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,012
So this is it, huh?

53
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:44,224
Up to the sky and over
the rainbow, wasn't it?

54
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:47,477
♪

55
00:03:47,477 --> 00:03:48,895
What's up, peeps?

56
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,564
I'm kinda new
to this Kyoto thing.

57
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:52,858
The tourist guide said
they have some famous

58
00:03:52,858 --> 00:03:55,277
archery contest
in this big temple

59
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:57,028
with 33 pillars
or something.

60
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:58,905
Is that what this is?

61
00:03:58,905 --> 00:03:59,948
Just kidding!

62
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:02,117
In this challenge,
the riders build up speed

63
00:04:02,117 --> 00:04:03,410
over a 10‐meter runway,

64
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:07,497
then try to jump over
33 people laying side by side.

65
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,791
Whoever jumps the farthest wins.

66
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,877
You won't find this
in any tour guide,

67
00:04:11,877 --> 00:04:15,755
but this is Kyoto's specialty,
the Devil's 30‐30!

68
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:17,090
And for those of you
who don't know,

69
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:21,136
I'm DJ Blood, man,
emceein' for freein'.

70
00:04:21,136 --> 00:04:23,096
You're doing this
for free, thanks a lot.

71
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:25,223
Whoa, Mr. Producer, wait a sec.

72
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:28,018
I didn't mean I'm doin' it
for free in real life.

73
00:04:28,018 --> 00:04:31,438
Anime and reality
are different, you know?

74
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:34,941
First up, representin' Trident,

75
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:38,820
Yoshitsune, ha‐ha!

76
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:45,452
♪

77
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:48,455
It looks like he's not
using the Rumble Regalia.

78
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,124
Guess he thinks you suck.

79
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:52,709
I don't get it.

80
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:56,505
There isn't an advantage
to using normal ATs, is there?

81
00:04:56,505 --> 00:05:04,721
♪

82
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:08,266
This is the perfect opportunity
to break Sora's old record

83
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:11,436
and we've got a huge
audience to witness it, too.

84
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:14,314
Let's see how Ikki likes that.

85
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:17,692
♪

86
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:21,071
All right, let's do this.

87
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:31,665
♪

88
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:34,501
He's using Kazu's pose.

89
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:37,546
Lookin' good.

90
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:39,631
This guy's for real.

91
00:05:39,631 --> 00:05:46,304
♪

92
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:48,306
‐It's too low!
‐No way.

93
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,933
He can't!

94
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:56,314
♪

95
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:59,734
I'm gonna break Sora's
record, just watch me.

96
00:05:59,734 --> 00:06:02,112
34.2 meters.

97
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:06,908
He's totally bent over
backwards right on top of 'em!

98
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:09,160
♪

99
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,787
This is it!

100
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:16,376
♪

101
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:21,089
That crazy man just
flew, can you dig it?

102
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,257
♪

103
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:24,759
Holy crap.

104
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:28,847
Yet he was able to increase
the distance by rotating,

105
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:31,182
using his chest
as the focal point.

106
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,559
Right.

107
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:35,645
Because if he rotated around
his hips like you normally do,

108
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,689
he would have hit his friends.

109
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:40,483
That was one hell of a
jump from Yoshitsune.

110
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,320
But was it good enough
to beat the record?

111
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,489
‐33.18
‐Oh, so close!

112
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:49,576
All he needed was 34.3
and he would have beaten

113
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:51,328
Sora's old record.

114
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:55,248
Too bad, maybe next time!

115
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:59,628
Hmph, life's a bitch.

116
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:01,087
Now it's your turn.

117
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,465
Let's see what you got, kid.

118
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:04,883
Oh?

119
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:08,303
What's he looking at?

120
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,931
When I was little,

121
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:15,685
I thought if I climbed all the
way to the top of the tower,

122
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:18,438
then I'd be able
to see anything,

123
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:21,024
no matter how far away it was.

124
00:07:21,024 --> 00:07:24,444
♪

125
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:26,488
Hey, Ikki?

126
00:07:26,488 --> 00:07:28,990
Do you know why you and me
don't have a mommy and daddy

127
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:31,117
like all the other kids?

128
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,410
Nuh‐uh.

129
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:34,245
We have different
last names too, right?

130
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:36,539
Why do we live
in the same house?

131
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,249
I dunno.

132
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:39,250
What happened?

133
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,127
Where are our
mommies and daddies?

134
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,837
Like I said, I dunno.

135
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:44,464
‐(screeching)
‐Huh?

136
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:47,717
It's North Star.

137
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:50,136
Guess he's looking for food.

138
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:53,765
Bye, North Star,
see you later!

139
00:07:53,765 --> 00:07:56,768
Buh‐bye!

140
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:58,353
I guess we better hurry home.

141
00:07:58,353 --> 00:08:02,357
I sure don't want Rika
to suplex me again.

142
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:03,733
You know what, Ikki?

143
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:04,859
Huh?

144
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:07,821
The whole world
all shares one sky.

145
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,490
♪

146
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,785
I bet if we could fly
as high as North Star,

147
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:17,163
we could look down and find
our mommies and daddies.

148
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:24,295
♪

149
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:27,090
‐Ikki.
‐Ikki!

150
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,800
You better make it!

151
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,969
They've got all the
Storm Riders from back home,

152
00:08:30,969 --> 00:08:32,637
how cool is that?

153
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:36,141
I'm not laying on the end,
you lay on the end.

154
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:37,934
(squabbling)

155
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:42,647
Whoa, that's quite
a blow for the Crow.

156
00:08:42,647 --> 00:08:46,484
Even his friends don't
have any faith in him.

157
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,944
Huh?

158
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:55,994
♪

159
00:08:55,994 --> 00:08:58,079
It's all right.

160
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,040
I know you can do it.

161
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,167
♪

162
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:04,794
I don't care what
anyone else thinks.

163
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:06,129
♪

164
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:08,590
Well, it took long enough,

165
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:11,009
but it looks like
they finally lined up.

166
00:09:11,009 --> 00:09:15,889
Will the Crow fly,
or will the Crow fail?

167
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:25,356
♪

168
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:28,151
Everyone here
is staring me down.

169
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:29,778
They don't think I can do it.

170
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:31,196
And they won't
respect me as a leader

171
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:32,697
until I prove them wrong,

172
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:34,741
until I show them
that I'm the best.

173
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:36,159
Hey, wake up.

174
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:37,827
It's time to jump.

175
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:38,953
You scared?

176
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:42,707
This is your last
chance to run away.

177
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,250
Yeah.

178
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,627
I can do this.

179
00:09:45,627 --> 00:09:47,337
Just watch.

180
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,047
You better take off
that stupid eye patch,

181
00:09:49,047 --> 00:09:53,218
'cause you're gonna wanna
see this with both eyes, yeah!

182
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,638
Huh‐‐the Regalia!

183
00:09:56,638 --> 00:10:01,643
♪

184
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:03,478
Heads, up, Crow!

185
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:06,356
The Fang Regalia!

186
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:08,566
So that's why he
asked me to bring it.

187
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:10,944
He had this planned
from the beginning.

188
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:18,785
♪

189
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:21,329
This is freakin' awesome!

190
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:23,748
♪

191
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:26,668
What?

192
00:10:26,668 --> 00:10:29,754
No, my Fang!

193
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:33,174
Son of a bitch!

194
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,760
No, the wind's disappearing!

195
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,972
He's sucking it into his ATs!

196
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:41,432
(yelling)

197
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:45,687
(shout)

198
00:10:45,687 --> 00:10:48,439
(crowd screams)

199
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:51,109
Ikki!

200
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:53,027
(scream)

201
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:58,575
♪

202
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:08,251
♪

203
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:11,129
Oh yeah, baby, plug
me in and turn me on.

204
00:11:11,129 --> 00:11:12,839
What, commercial break's over?

205
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:14,048
We back now?

206
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,508
Oh, sorry.

207
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:17,010
What the hell just happened?

208
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:20,513
The Crow was soaring one second,
then his ride disappeared

209
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:23,099
and he got blasted to the curb.

210
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:25,810
Are you okay?

211
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,979
Like a windmill.

212
00:11:27,979 --> 00:11:29,564
I get it now.

213
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:31,316
♪

214
00:11:31,316 --> 00:11:33,484
It's the Rumble Regalia's power.

215
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,111
It operates on
the same principle

216
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,821
as a Ram Jet or windmill.

217
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:40,325
I see, that Regalia needs
a strong opposing wind.

218
00:11:40,325 --> 00:11:42,827
The stronger
the surging wind is,

219
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:45,580
the more the
acceleration increases.

220
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,540
Which would explain
why he didn't use it

221
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,667
for the jump he made earlier.

222
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:56,841
♪

223
00:11:56,841 --> 00:11:59,260
I suggest you stop right there.

224
