Outside interference
is forbidden

225
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,805
in a battle like this.

226
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:04,432
Oh yeah?

227
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,851
Well, you better watch where
you stick that leg of yours,

228
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,937
'cause I bite.

229
00:12:08,937 --> 00:12:12,232
Yeah, fine with me,
I'll bite you right back.

230
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,901
You stupid little punks!

231
00:12:14,901 --> 00:12:17,946
I've had about enough
of your bullshit.

232
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:20,323
If you can't show some
respect for Kansai,

233
00:12:20,323 --> 00:12:22,867
then go home!

234
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,078
Listen, shithead,
the Devil's 30‐30

235
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,622
is about more than just ATs.

236
00:12:27,622 --> 00:12:30,250
You gotta have balls to do this,
you've gotta have trust,

237
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,043
you've gotta have courage.

238
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:33,544
♪

239
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:36,798
But obviously, you're
too stupid to grasp that.

240
00:12:36,798 --> 00:12:39,175
♪

241
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,094
Did you really think
I wouldn't notice

242
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:43,179
you were using the Fang?

243
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,181
♪

244
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:48,059
It's scary as hell, I know.

245
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:51,562
Even pros lose their nerve
on a jump like this.

246
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,523
But that's only natural
when your friends are

247
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:55,149
lying right under you.

248
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:56,484
Still, you can't give up.

249
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,278
You gotta keep your
legs from shaking

250
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:01,114
and you gotta stop your heart
from beating out of your chest.

251
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:03,908
And if you've got
the balls to do that,

252
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:07,412
if you've got the courage
to make that jump,

253
00:13:07,412 --> 00:13:09,414
then that explains
why people are willing

254
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:12,500
to follow you
in the first place.

255
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,544
But more than that,
it shows you why

256
00:13:14,544 --> 00:13:16,129
they're willing to lie down,

257
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:20,008
why they're willing to put
their lives on the line for you.

258
00:13:20,008 --> 00:13:22,385
Someone like you probably
wouldn't even notice,

259
00:13:22,385 --> 00:13:26,264
but the whole starting platform
is covered in little scratches.

260
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:27,390
Huh?

261
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:29,142
♪

262
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:31,352
They were made in honor of
the people who were willing

263
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:34,272
to entrust their lives
to their friends.

264
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:37,275
This platform is a monument
to the faith that they had

265
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:39,485
in their leader.

266
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,487
I'm not about to let
a little shit like you

267
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,114
leave his mark on it,

268
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:44,657
so get the hell out of here.

269
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,200
If that's what you're made of,
then you don't have

270
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,703
what it takes to be a leader.

271
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:49,787
I'm through with you.

272
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,080
I'm sorry.

273
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,583
Hm?

274
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:54,625
Huh?

275
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:55,585
No way!

276
00:13:55,585 --> 00:13:57,503
Did he just...

277
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:59,005
Apologize?

278
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,131
What a load of crap.

279
00:14:00,131 --> 00:14:01,591
What's going on?

280
00:14:01,591 --> 00:14:03,092
It's a sign of the apocalypse.

281
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,802
Well, he's freakin' me out.

282
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:08,264
I'm sorry, I was wrong.

283
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:12,018
And everything you just
said is true, but...

284
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:15,980
please, I'm begging you,
let me jump one more time.

285
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:19,567
Please!

286
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:29,744
♪

287
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,162
Oh, sure!

288
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:32,663
As long as you understand.

289
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:35,291
In fact, you can jump as many
times as you would like.

290
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,793
What, just like that?

291
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:38,086
So, is he mad or not?

292
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:41,172
Wow, I didn't know
Yoshitsune was so nice.

293
00:14:41,172 --> 00:14:44,342
Looks like the Crow gets
another chance to fly.

294
00:14:44,342 --> 00:14:46,427
(yelling)

295
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:50,264
♪

296
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:52,725
He didn't even try
to jump that time.

297
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,852
What is he up to?

298
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:57,021
‐This is bad.
‐I know.

299
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,481
It must have happened
when he twisted around

300
00:14:58,481 --> 00:15:01,692
to stop himself from
crashing into that girl.

301
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:04,237
He landed on that
knee pretty hard.

302
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:06,823
I bet it hurts so bad
he can barely stand.

303
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:08,658
♪

304
00:15:08,658 --> 00:15:10,368
‐Ikki!
‐Stay back!

305
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,954
♪

306
00:15:12,954 --> 00:15:14,247
Ikki.

307
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:15,998
I‐‐I guess I just
slipped on something

308
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:17,083
and lost my footing.

309
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:19,210
I'm sorry, please,
can I do it again?

310
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:21,337
Sure, do whatever you want.

311
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:23,214
♪

312
00:15:23,214 --> 00:15:24,966
Something isn't right.

313
00:15:24,966 --> 00:15:27,593
♪

314
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:30,012
Hey, wait a minute,
not on my chest!

315
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:32,390
♪

316
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,517
Well, this is just
getting stupid.

317
00:15:34,517 --> 00:15:35,726
It's too much.

318
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,520
This is too hard to watch!

319
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:43,651
♪

320
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:46,654
I've never seen Ikki
like this before.

321
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,239
It's incredible.

322
00:15:48,239 --> 00:15:50,741
I feel like he's growing
stronger and stronger

323
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:51,909
with every jump.

324
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:54,453
♪

325
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:58,416
Watching him like this,
it makes me happy.

326
00:15:58,416 --> 00:16:00,543
But I feel a little sad too.

327
00:16:00,543 --> 00:16:03,296
It's almost like
he's leaving me behind.

328
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:06,257
I want him to win,
but it hurts.

329
00:16:06,257 --> 00:16:08,593
I don't know what
to think anymore.

330
00:16:08,593 --> 00:16:10,678
♪

331
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:12,430
I hate to see it end this way,

332
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:14,765
but it looks to me
like this is it.

333
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:16,934
All according to your plan, huh?

334
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:18,644
You've seen the Rumble Regalia.

335
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,480
That's what you wanted, right?

336
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:24,066
You can be as
ambitious as you'd like.

337
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,943
I don't care.

338
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,528
But I tell you one thing:

339
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:28,988
If you keep thinking like that,

340
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:32,825
you'll never be a king
for as long as you ride.

341
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,619
Not bad, you're almost there.

342
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:36,579
Why not move out of the way?

343
00:16:36,579 --> 00:16:37,788
I don't understand.

344
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:40,124
How can he keep this up
with an injured knee?

345
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:41,459
I guess that's the difference

346
00:16:41,459 --> 00:16:43,794
between a guy who's
destined to be king

347
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:45,129
and you.

348
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:47,048
While you're sitting
here on the ground

349
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:48,341
picking things apart

350
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:50,468
and thinking about how you
can take advantage of people,

351
00:16:50,468 --> 00:16:53,888
he's only thinking
about one thing:

352
00:16:53,888 --> 00:16:55,556
the sky.

353
00:16:55,556 --> 00:17:01,354
♪

354
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:02,772
Even all the way up here,

355
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:06,275
I still can't find
my mommy and daddy.

356
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:07,360
But when I look down,

357
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,320
I feel like I could
walk on the clouds

358
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:13,282
and keep walking,
forever and ever.

359
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:14,408
‐Huh?
‐Gotcha!

360
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,409
Take us up!

361
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:16,369
Riko, we gotta stop him.

362
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:19,330
Yeah, I'm worried
about his knee!

363
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,498
(scream)

364
00:17:20,498 --> 00:17:21,832
It's too late now.

365
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:23,793
He already has his wings.

366
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:24,794
Huh?

367
00:17:24,794 --> 00:17:26,003
Ever since he was young,

368
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:28,464
I've always been afraid
of him realizing that

369
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,841
and flying away.

370
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:34,011
But now, I can't
deny it anymore.

371
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:37,682
And no matter how much
we sit and worry about him...

372
00:17:37,682 --> 00:17:41,852
those wings will always
call him back to the sky.

373
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:44,689
I thought the battle
would have ended by now.

374
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:45,898
Glad we made it.

375
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,858
I wanna see my little Crow fly.

376
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:49,193
But if Ikki loses,

377
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:51,195
he won't just bring
shame to Genesis.

378
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:54,031
He'll make everyone
in Kanto look bad.

379
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:56,117
And believe me,
that wouldn't be good.

380
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:57,493
Come on.

381
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:59,996
Do you really think
that'll happen?

382
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:01,497
All right!

383
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:05,376
The density of wind is
much higher than still air.

384
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:07,128
If he can ride its
pressure gradient,

385
00:18:07,128 --> 00:18:10,381
he can lift his body
up even higher.

386
00:18:10,381 --> 00:18:13,676
Normal people can't detect
something as subtle as that,

387
00:18:13,676 --> 00:18:15,219
but this kid is different,

388
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:18,389
he feels it with
every inch of his skin.

389
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,892
It's easy to call it talent,
but it's more than that.

390
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,769
How should I say it, it's like

391
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:28,065
he's finally discovered
his true wings.

392
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,567
Kazu, move your ass!

393
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:32,695
‐Way ahead of you.
‐Ditto.

394
00:18:32,695 --> 00:18:34,572
You finally made it
down here, huh?

395
00:18:34,572 --> 00:18:36,032
'Bout damn time.

396
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:37,742
(chuckles)

397
00:18:37,742 --> 00:18:38,826
Almost.

398
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,788
He's changed.

399
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,874
You're saying he's
qualified to be king

400
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:48,210
because of that winged
shadow behind him?

401
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,211
Are you kidding?

402
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:51,005
You still don't get it, do you?

403
00:18:51,005 --> 00:18:53,257
Aeon, do you know
why ATs are different

404
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:56,135
from skateboards
and things like that?

405
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:59,347
Because with ATs,
you can fly.

406
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:01,474
But although we follow
different roads,

407
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:02,975
we all ride the wind,

408
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,478
because we all
share the same sky.

409
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:08,606
We call it the
Infinite Atmosphere,

410
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:11,150
the power that allows us to fly.

411
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,027
Every regalia
and every technique

412
00:19:13,027 --> 00:19:15,404
relies on the wind in some way.

413
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:18,032
Of course, that goes
for my Rumble Reglia

414
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:19,617
and his Fang Regalia,

415
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:24,205
as well as Spitfire's Flame
Regalia and Nue's Thunder.

416
00:19:24,205 --> 00:19:27,249
Actually, the number of kings
isn't limited to eight.

417
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:29,085
It's just that there have
only been eight roads

418
00:19:29,085 --> 00:19:32,546
with the power to find
the true path to the sky.

419
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:35,800
So it's no surprise
that Simca wants Ikki.

420
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,511
Since the Wing Road calls
on the power of the wind,

421
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,596
it's central to all
the different roads

422
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:42,640
leading to the top.

423
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,266
(crowd cheering)

424
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:47,144
Is this one of your
strategies you're so proud of?

425
00:19:47,144 --> 00:19:49,772
You're hoping that
Ikki's power will awaken,

426
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:53,317
and then he'll challenge Genesis
just like he said he would.

427
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:56,487
And after the battle,
both teams will be weakened,

428
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:59,240
with Trident remaining
untouched, of course.

429
00:20:01,242 --> 00:20:03,828
Well, maybe so.

430
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:05,871
But I felt like you
were leading him astray

431
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:08,999
with all that talk about
being your new boss.

432
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:11,377
I guess you could say
I just wanted to remind him

433
00:20:11,377 --> 00:20:14,171
what riding ATs
is really about.

434
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:16,799
♪

435
00:20:16,799 --> 00:20:18,134
I guess we'll see.

436
00:20:18,134 --> 00:20:20,469
Oh, Agito.

437
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:22,722
‐What's in the bag?
‐Your clothes.

438
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:24,640
Are you saying...

439
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:27,560
you've had my clothes?

440
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,938
‐I've been holding them for you.
‐Why didn't you say so?

441
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,940
I just did.

442
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,484
You mean, you don't
enjoy dressing like that?

443
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:38,446
♪

444
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:40,072
Hey, Crow?

445
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:43,868
♪

446
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:44,994
Agito.

447
00:20:44,994 --> 00:20:47,496
I thought we both could
use a change of clothes.

448
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:48,581
Aw, come on.

449
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:50,666
I thought you were
a bitchin' bride.

450
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:52,084
Fuck you!

451
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:54,044
Do it for the team.

452
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:56,046
We're all counting on you.

453
00:20:56,046 --> 00:21:07,933
♪

454
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,436
I don't know where he
gets all that power from.

455
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:12,897
I've never seen anyone that's
only been riding for two months

456
00:21:12,897 --> 00:21:15,357
show this much potential.

457
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:16,901
He barely started,
and that little bastard

458
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:20,571
already has the strength
to touch the sky.

459
00:21:20,571 --> 00:21:22,907
(crowd cheering)

460
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:26,535
♪

461
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:28,996
Come on, Ikki,
you can do it!

462
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:30,623
I've never seen
anything like it.

463
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:34,001
That punk's even got his
enemies cheering for him now.

464
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:36,921
All it takes is one more jump.

465
00:21:36,921 --> 00:21:39,632
Then he'll prove his worth
as a Sky King candidate

466
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:42,718
and claim his right to
rule over all of Genesis,

467
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:44,136
and all the riders in Japan‐‐

468
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:46,514
no, all the riders
in the bloody world

469
00:21:46,514 --> 00:21:49,433
will be watching
when it happens.

470
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:52,019
Yeah, but all Ikki
cares about is flying.

471
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,271
None of that stuff
matters to him.

472
00:21:54,271 --> 00:21:57,191
All I know is that
Ikki was born to fly,

473
00:21:57,191 --> 00:22:00,402
as high and as far
as the wind will take him.

474
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:01,695
Oh, hey, by the way,

475
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:03,656
can you do something
with my hair?

476
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:05,658
I'm rethinking
cutting it this short.

477
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:07,117
Sorry, love, no refunds.

478
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:08,452
Ikki?

479
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:16,460
♪

480
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:17,711
Huh?

481
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:19,630
Wait, why are you standing up?

482
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:21,131
You know, remember?

483
00:22:21,131 --> 00:22:22,925
When Ikki makes
a face like that‐‐

484
00:22:22,925 --> 00:22:24,718
We have nothing to worry about.

485
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:26,595
Buccha, your ass
is in my face!

486
00:22:26,595 --> 00:22:28,806
‐I get it.
‐Oh yeah, baby.

487
00:22:28,806 --> 00:22:30,599
‐Hope you're right.
‐Now I remember.

488
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:32,893
Kogarasumaru!

489
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:34,311
(screeches)

490
00:22:34,311 --> 00:22:36,689
Kill 'em dead!

491
00:22:36,689 --> 00:22:42,027
♪

492
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:43,279
That's right.

493
00:22:43,279 --> 00:22:45,865
This started a long time ago.

494
00:22:45,865 --> 00:22:47,116
From the beginning,

495
00:22:47,116 --> 00:22:49,910
Ikki has always been
one with the sky.

496
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:56,333
♪

497
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:58,419
And ever since that day...

498
00:22:58,419 --> 00:23:02,339
♪

499
00:23:02,339 --> 00:23:04,842
Ikki!

500
00:23:04,842 --> 00:23:07,052
He's flying!

501
00:23:09,013 --> 00:23:11,348
He's flying!

502
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:14,184
He's always been my hero,

503
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:16,520
and he always will be.

504
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:19,815
♪

505
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:24,236
(beep)

506
00:23:30,701 --> 00:23:32,453
Ringo!

507
00:23:32,453 --> 00:23:34,204
Ringo, you see that?

508
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:36,040
I'm a genius.

509
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:39,043
And I've got superpowers, too.

510
00:23:39,043 --> 00:23:40,044
(chuckles)

511
00:23:40,044 --> 00:23:41,420
Right.

